'''Joel Leandro Ordóñez Guerrero''' (born 21 April 2004) is an Ecuadorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].

==Club career==

=== Independiente del Valle ===
Ordóñez is a youth product of [[Deportivo Azogues]] and [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle|Independiente del Valle]]. He began his senior career with Independiente del Valle in 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.msn.com/fr-be/sport/football/le-club-de-bruges-suivrait-un-jeune-d%C3%A9fenseur-central-%C3%A9quatorien/ar-AAZUN6q|title=Le Club de Bruges suivrait un jeune défenseur central équatorien|website=MSN}}</ref> He made his senior and professional debut for them in a 0–0 [[Ecuadorian Serie A]] draw with [[Guayaquil City F.C.|Guayaquil City]] on 9 April 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.benditofutbol.com/legionarios/joel-ordonez-quinto-ecuatoriano-belgica.html|title=Joel Ordóñez, quinto ecuatoriano en Bélgica|website=Bendito Futbol|access-date=23 January 2023|archive-date=23 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230123195633/https://www.benditofutbol.com/legionarios/joel-ordonez-quinto-ecuatoriano-belgica.html|url-status=dead}}</ref>

=== Club Brugge ===
On 2 August 2022, Ordóñez joined [[Belgian Pro League]] side [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] for a reported fee of €4 million, initially being assigned to [[Club NXT]], their reserve side in the [[Challenger Pro League]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-08-02 |title=OFFICIEEL: Club Brugge betaalt miljoenen voor toptalent Ordonez |url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.be/nieuws/1040711/officieel-club-brugge-betaalt-miljoenen-voor-toptalent-ordonez.html |access-date=2025-09-16 |website=VoetbalPrimeur.be |language=nl-NL}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Club NXT in a 1–0 win at home against [[R.E. Virton|Virton]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-16 |title=Joel Ordóñez |url=https://www.clubbrugge.be/en/teams/a-kern/players/joel-ord%C3%B3%C3%B1ez |access-date=2025-09-16 |website=Club Brugge |language=en}}</ref> On 19 August 2022, Ordóñez was promoted to the senior team of Club Brugge.

On 16 September 2025, Ordóñez extended his contract with Club Brugge until 2029.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-09-16 |title=Joel Ordóñez extends his stay at Club Brugge until 2029 |url=https://www.clubbrugge.be/en/news/joel-ord%C3%B3%C3%B1ez-verlengt-tot-2029-bij-club-brugge-637028 |access-date=2025-09-16 |website=Club Brugge |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
Ordóñez first represented Ecuador internationally with the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador U15]]s as captain at the [[2019 South American U-15 Championship]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sport.de/fussball/pe609447/joel-ordonez/co5513/campeonato-sudamericano/spiele-als-spieler/|title=Joel Ordóñez – Spielüberblick U15 Campeonato Sudamericano|website=sport.de}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Ecuador national under-20 football team|Ecuador U20]]s for the [[South American Youth Football Championship]], but was not released by his club for the tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/estos-son-los-ecuatorianos-que-estan-en-el-extranjero-y-no-fueron-convocados-para-el-sudamericano-sub-20-colombia-2023-nota/|title=Estos son los ecuatorianos que están en el extranjero y no fueron convocados para el Sudamericano Sub-20 Colombia 2023|date=9 January 2023|website=El Universo}}</ref> He made his debut for Ecuador on 21 March 2024, starting and playing the full 90 minutes in a 2–0 friendly match victory against [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-03-22 |title=John Yeboah, Alan Minda, Joel Ordóñez y Allen Obando debutaron en Ecuador ante Guatemala |url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/futbol/mundial/nota/_/id/13408705/yeboah-minda-ordonez-obando-debutantes-ecuador-guatemala |access-date=2025-09-16 |website=ESPNdeportes.com |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Ecuador v Guatemala |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c4nvkglx9n2t |access-date=2025-09-16 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

